le/henrygomez/rep-tim-ryan-is-heading-to-iowa-and-new-hampshire-as-he\">confirmed</a> he’ll be taking additional trips out there in the coming weeks. In his interview with Burnett Wednesday, the moderate Democrat struck a call for unity that sounded a lot like a campaign theme: “You can’t win the future divided,” he said.</p>\n<p>Ryan, who has served in the House since 2003, drew significant national attention in 2016 when he mounted an unsuccessful bid to unseat <strong>Nancy Pelosi</strong> and lead Democrats in Congress. At the time, <strong>Donald Trump</strong> had just won Ryan’s home county in Ohio by 7 points&#8212;a 30-point swing from the previous election, when <strong>Barack Obama</strong> won by 23&#8212;the first Republican to do so in more than four decades. Ryan had positioned himself as someone who could stop the Democrats’ bleeding in previously blue areas that had gone to Trump in 2016. “As I saw the blue firewall collapse, I was like: I need to step up,” he <a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/powerpost/wp/2016/11/29/meet-tim-ryan-the-ohio-democrat-challenging-nancy-pelosi-for-control-of-house-democrats/\">told</a> <em>The Washington Post</em> at the time. “I need to be a bigger voice in the party.”</p>\n<p>He will likely take a similar position if he joins the race, tacking closer to the center than other 2020 challengers. That could give him some appeal among moderates, but it’s unclear how he’d be received by the party’s insurgent progressive sect. Ryan could also be overshadowed by more prominent Midwestern challengers like <strong>Amy Klobuchar,</strong> the Minnesota senator who <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/02/amy-klobuchar-you-bet-your-ass-im-a-tough-boss\">announced her bid</a> last week, and <strong>Sherrod Brown,</strong> the Ohio senator who has also been <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/sherrod-brown-2020-race-chances\">publicly flirting</a> with a run. Like Ryan, Brown is short on name recognition, but his appeal among both centrists and progressives could elevate his national profile. It’s not yet clear whether Ryan would be able to do the same.</p>\n<h3>More Great Stories from <em>Vanity Fair</em></h3>\n<p>&#8212; The leaking, gossiping, and infighting that <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/trump-aide-recalls-conways-leaking-tactics-in-the-west-wing-vipers-nest?inline\">made Kellyanne Conway a formidable White House player</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Why old news habits must die&#8212;so that <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/how-the-media-can-prevent-2020-from-becoming-2016?inline\">real journalism can live</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Nancy Pelosi is America’s most powerful <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/style/photos/2019/01/nancy-pelosi-power-suits?inline\">power-suit boss</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Is Kamala Harris the <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/kamala-harris-new-2020-democratic-frontrunner-oakland-speech?inline\">2020 candidate to beat?</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Your passport to <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/behind-the-scenes-hollywood-cover-2019?inline\"><em>Vanity Fair</em>’s 25th Hollywood Issue</a> with Saoirse Ronan, Timothée Chalamet, Chadwick Boseman, and more</p>\n<p>Looking for more? <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/newsletters\">Sign up</a> for our daily Hive newsletter and never miss a story.</p>","rubric":"Democrats 2020","socialTitle":"Pelosi Frenemy Tim Ryan “Seriously” Considering Presidential Bid","socialDescription":"Yet another Midwestern moderate is toying with a 2020 run.","seoTitle":"Pelosi Frenemy Tim Ryan “Seriously” Considering Presidential Bid","seoDescription":"Yet another Midwestern moderate is toying with a 2020 run.","channel":"News","subChannel":"Politics","issueDate":"","ledeCaption":"","contentSource":"web","canonicalUrl":"","interactiveOverride":"","contentType":"","textMimeType":"","tags":["tim ryan","democrats 2020","politics","nancy pelosi"],"revisio