s with quite a “surprise, bitch”: <strong>Emma Roberts</strong> will be back for Season 9, the <em>A.H.S.</em> maestro said, with skier and Olympic medalist <strong>Gus Kenworthy</strong> also on board to play her boyfriend.</p>\n<p>Murphy shared the news on Instagram, where he posted a photo of Kenworthy captioned, “That special moment when you realize you have an Olympic medal AND will be playing Emma Roberts’ boyfriend on ‘American Horror Story’ Season 9.”</p>\n<div class=\"embed block social-instagram row\"><blockquote class=\"embed instagram-embed-component instagram-media \" data-instgrm-captioned=\"true\" data-instgrm-version=\"2\" data-type=\"instagram\" data-url=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BtjKS5nhIvO/\"><div class=\"instagram-media-container\"><div class=\"instagram-media-wrapper\"><div class=\"instagram-media-inner\"><div class=\"instagram-media-view\"></div><span class=\"instagram-media-loading\">Loading</span></div></div><p class=\"instagram-media-more\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BtjKS5nhIvO/\" target=\"blank\">View on Instagram</a></p></div></blockquote></div><p>This will be Roberts’s fifth season on the show. In Season 3, she played the <em>Coven</em> witch Madison Montgomery&#8212;a role she reprised in the show’s most recent season, <em>Apocalypse.</em> She also played the devious Maggie Esmerelda in <em>Freak Show</em> and journalist Serena Belinda in <em>Cult.</em> Season 9 will be Kenworthy’s first appearance on the show, but it’s unclear what he’ll be doing, beyond acting as Roberts’s screen boyfriend, or how much screen time he’ll get.</p>\n<p><em>A.H.S.: Apocalypse</em> was, overall, a <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/10/american-horror-story-apocalypse-episode-4-recap-witches-warlocks-michael-langdon\">return to campy form</a> for the series, even if it didn’t <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/11/american-horror-story-apocalypse-finale-recap-mallory-michael\">quite</a> stick the landing. Fans of the long-running horror series often strongly disagree about which seasons have been the show’s best, and which are the worst&#8212;but at least <em>Apocalypse</em> always had fun. So far, no details are known regarding what the plan for Season 9 might be, including its general subject. Hopefully within a few months, fans will at least have a theme to guess and theorize about&#8212;but for now, at least we know that Roberts will be back, probably to play another delightful brat.</p>\n<h3>More Great Stories from <em>Vanity Fair</em></h3>\n<p>&#8212; The <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/02/the-worst-kept-secret-of-trumps-presidency?inline\">worst-kept secret</a> of Trump’s presidency</p>\n<p>&#8212; Is Silicon Valley suffocating the media? <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/how-google-and-facebook-are-strangling-their-digital-offspring?inline\">Jill Abramson weighs in</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Bernie Sanders’s <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/bernie-sanders-estate-tax-billionaires?inline\">plan to eat the rich</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; The 25 <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/25-best-movie-scenes?inline\">most influential movie scenes</a> of the past 25 years</p>\n<p>&#8212; <em>Broad City</em> and the <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/01/broad-city-millennial-rage-ilana-glazer-abbi-jacobson?inline\">pivot to millennial rage</a></p>\n<p>Looking for more? <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/newsletters\">Sign up</a> for our daily Hollywood newsletter and never miss a story.</p>","rubric":"the horror, the horror!","socialTitle":"American Horror Story Season 9 Will Bring Back Emma Roberts","socialDescription":"Ryan Murphy has announced two cast members for the upcoming season, but beyond that, details remain shrouded in mystery.","seoTitle":"American Horror Story Season 9 Will Bring Back Emma Roberts","seoDescription":"Ryan Murphy has announced two cast members for the upcoming season, but beyo