d their former-presidential-candidate spouses enjoy a good date night on the town. On Tuesday evening, <strong>Hillary</strong> and <strong>Bill Clinton,</strong> among a slew of other famous names, headed to the Samuel J. Friedman Theatre in Manhattan for the opening night of <em>Choir Boy,</em> written by <em>Moonlight</em> scribe <strong>Tarell Alvin McCraney.</strong> The Clintons hammed it up for photographers, smiling and showing off the playbill. <strong>Cynthia Erivo,</strong> <strong>Debra Messing,</strong> <strong>Phylicia Rashad,</strong> and more also joined for the play’s debut.</p>\n<p>Hillary has kept a relatively low profile as of late, giving the occasional speech and responding to <strong>Donald Trump’s</strong> presidency online. But in a show of her much-discussed superhuman work ethic, she took to Twitter once the play was over. She wrote about Trump’s Oval Office address and his hopes for a wall at the U.S.-Mexico border in a <a href=\"https://twitter.com/HillaryClinton/status/1083029073230729218\">series of tweets</a>, disputing what she called a “ridiculous” speech.</p>\n<p>“The only border crisis we’re facing is the inhumane detention of kids that has already led to the deaths of two children,” she wrote, linking to an ActBlue charity fund.</p>\n<p>She added: “We’ve raised over $100k and counting for organizations that help families and kids at the border since the beginning of the president’s TV stunt last night. Let’s keep counteracting his lies about migrants and refugees with positive action.”</p>\n<p>Hillary also <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2019/01/the-new-congressional-class-set-a-high-style-bar\">showed support</a> for the women sworn into Congress last week, the most in United States history, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/HillaryClinton/status/1080941776377180160\">writing</a>, “To the women sworn in to Congress today, the most in our history: Congratulations. Knock it out of the park.”</p>\n<p>She has yet to tweet her thoughts on <em>Choir Boy,</em> but others are giving it positive reviews.</p>\n<h3>More Great Stories from <em>Vanity Fair</em></h3>\n<p>&#8212; Nothing says grace like <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2019/01/justin-bieber-face-tattoo-grace?inline\">Justin Bieber’s face tattoo</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Meghan Markle’s <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/12/inside-the-meghan-markle-family-breakdown-thomas-samantha-markle?inline\">fractured family story</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Inside Trump’s <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/trump-marla-and-the-epic-battle-for-mar-a-lago?inline\">epic battle for Mar-a-Lago</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Saoirse Ronan’s <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/12/saoirse-ronan-mary-queen-of-scots-little-women?inline\">Hollywood lessons</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; How Facebook and Amazon are turning life into <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/how-facebook-amazon-and-others-are-turning-life-into-a-horrific-bradbury-novel?inline\">sci-fi dystopia</a></p>\n<p>Looking for more? <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/newsletters\">Sign up</a> for our daily newsletter and never miss a story.</p>","rubric":"Keeping the Flame Alive","socialTitle":"The Clintons Have a Broadway Date Night During Trump’s “Ridiculous” Speech","socialDescription":"Hillary and Bill Clinton opted to go to the opening night of Choir Boy during the president’s Oval Office address, but it didn’t keep the former secretary of state off Twitter.","seoTitle":"The Clintons Have a Broadway Date Night During Trump’s “Ridiculous” Speech","seoDescription":"Hillary and Bill Clinton opted to go to the opening night of Choir Boy during the president’s Oval Office address, but it didn’t keep the former secretary of state off Twitter.","channel":"Style","subChannel":"Celebrity","issueDate":"","ledeCaption":"","contentSource":"web","canonicalUrl":"","contentType":"","textMimeType":"","tags":[],"revisionAuthor":"Erin Vanderhoof","meta":{"collectionNa