emained anonymous, told <em>The Sun</em>: “I was asked by a police minder not to take a photo of the children, which I didn’t, but George started stroking my dog.” What does one do when the most famous five-year-old in the world comes up to you and your dog and starts petting the animal? Well, in this woman’s case, she&#8212;understandably unsure what to say, probably&#8212;blurted out the first question that came to mind. “Just to be friendly, I engaged in a bit of small talk, and I asked George what his name was, even though obviously I knew it,” she said.</p>\n<p>George’s response, however, was a bit surprising. She recounted, “To my astonishment, he said, ‘I’m called Archie,’ with a big smile on his face. I don’t know why he calls himself Archie, but kids often play with their names, and I think it’s lovely.”</p>\n<p>Why Archie?! As we wondered earlier, maybe George dressed as the comic-book character for Halloween last year, and this is sort of a residual “bit” he’s been doing since? The <em>Daily Mail</em> notes that George’s middle names are Alexander and Louis, so perhaps it’s possible Archie emerged as some sort of variation of Alexander? Or maybe it’s some sort of layered inside joke with Charlotte, where they pretend they’re “ordinary” kids with alternate normal lives when they come across strangers, just to amuse themselves.</p>","rubric":"Royals","socialTitle":"Has Prince George’s Unexpected Nickname Been Revealed?","socialDescription":"“I was asked by a police minder not to take a photo of the children . . . but George started stroking my dog.”\n","seoTitle":"Has Prince George’s Unexpected Nickname Been Revealed?","seoDescription":"“I was asked by a police minder not to take a photo of the children . . . but George started stroking my dog.”\n","channel":"Style","subChannel":"Royals","issueDate":"","ledeCaption":"","contentSource":"web","canonicalUrl":"","interactiveOverride":"","contentType":"","textMimeType":"","tags":["prince george"],"revisionAuthor