re Googling it and deciding there is <em>no way</em> you are doing something called “Whole30”), or perhaps you want to aim to read more books (translation: buy a bunch of books that will make for one great Instagram Story nightstand shot and then sit untouched for a few months). Given the trouble we have keeping our own resolutions, it is pretty absurd for us to come up with them for others, but we are going to do so anyway&#8212;for some of our more cherished VF.com celebrities.</p>\n<p><strong>Justin Bieber:</strong> Release some new music! Something! Anything! We’ll even take an ode to your apparent <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2019/01/justin-bieber-face-tattoo-grace\">new face tattoo</a>. As amusing as all of the Bieber antics are (the hotel slippers! The <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/31/entertainment/jojo-siwa-justin-bieber-apology/index.html\">social-media spats</a> with 15-year-old YouTubers! Gallivanting across the globe with <strong>Hailey Baldwin</strong>!), it’s possible to forget the great success of his recent-ish pop hits (sorry, but “Sorry” holds up quite well). It’s been a while, Justin!</p>\n<p><strong>The Markle family:</strong> Take a breather from the press circuit. At first, we understood the impulse to want to tell “your side” of the story, but, at this point, it’s the same talking points over and over again, guys. We could basically pre-write the <strong>Thomas</strong> and <strong>Samantha Markle</strong> <em>Daily Mail</em> interviews at this point with 90 percent accuracy. Unless there is a major new perspective to share, it seems you guys would have the best chance of getting a response from <strong>Meghan</strong> if you laid low for a bit.</p>\n<p><strong>Julia Roberts:</strong> Turn on your Instagram comments. This is very specific and purely selfish on our part, but we (and many others, we are sure) have been wanting to comment on your (delightful, slightly offbeat) posts, even with just a few blue hearts or a straightforward “amazing!” . . . only to be reminded that comments have been turned off on your page. (Note: that said, we understand fully not wanting to deal with the grimy underworld of Instagram comments, Julia.)</p>\n<p><strong>Kate Middleton and Meghan Markle:</strong> Without knowing what’s actually going on with you guys, what about&#8212;as a P.R. move, if nothing else&#8212;“getting caught by the paparazzi” doing something low-key and fun and sister-in-law-y? A sushi lunch? Catching a matinee of <em>Second Act</em>? Whatever. It’d do so much to quell the incessant feud rumors, which would be nice for everyone, right? It’d be months of “Kate and Meg: Leaning on Each Other” and “Double Duchess: New B.F.F.s?!” tabloid covers.</p>\n<p><strong>The Palace:</strong> Give Meghan her Instagram account back! We’ve said it before; we’ll say it again. It’ll only <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2018/05/give-meghan-markle-her-instagram-account-back\">result in positives</a> for you guys.</p>\n<p><strong>Ariana Grande:</strong> Sign on for a lead film role, maybe in a romantic comedy? Following the success of her “Thank U, Next” music video, in which she embodied the protagonists of four famous rom-coms, what better next move for Grande (just announced as a Coachella headliner) than starring in a romantic comedy of her own? She has the acting background for it, and could provide the genre with a needed rejuvenating spark (maybe she could be cast against <strong>Noah Centineo</strong>?).</p>\n<p><strong>Jennifer Lawrence and Emma Stone:</strong> Star in a buddy comedy together. Real-life friends and two of our biggest movie stars, the actresses have not worked together on a project yet, to our disappointment. We’ll even take some sort of six-episode Amazon Prime limited-series situation! (Note: yes, we realize we have now annoyingly been banging this drum <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2014/12/new-years-resolutions-2015-emma-watson-jennifer-lawrence-kate-middleton\">since the end of 2014</a>.)</p>\n<p><strong>Rihanna:</strong> Yeah, yeah, everyone’s on your case about releasing music, which of course we are indeed desperate for. But what about hosting a late-night show? Can’t you see it? Rihanna, glass of <a href=\"https://www.thecut.com/2016/07/rihanna-wine-glasses-to-go-restaurants.html\">red wine in hand</a>, her crew seated behind her? Guests would come in and chat about Netflix shows and skin-care routines? It would be perfect.</p>\n<p><strong>Timothée Chalamet and Lily-Rose Depp:</strong> You guys have the potential to be our next great “style icon” couple, the sort teenagers obsess about on Tumblr and that we’ll post throwback pictures of in 2031 with captions like, “Remember the mid-2010s?” The more looks you guys deliver, the better! Go on lots of outings in paparazzi-friendly locales, please!</p>\n<p><strong>Prince George:</strong> We know he’s gifted at language (remember his very nuanced understanding of language cues at a <a href=\"https://people.com/royals/prince-george-looks-for-daddy-in-china-cabinet-after-hearing-prince-william-is-in-china/\">very young age</a>?) and we very much hope he’s keeping a journal of some kind, with its entries ideally to be published at a later date.</p>\n<p><strong>Cardi B:</strong> Volunteer to host the Oscars. We cannot think of anyone who would excite us more in that role.</p>","rubric":"Auld Lang Syne","socialTitle":"Suggested New Year’s Resolutions for Ariana Grande, Prince George, and More","socialDescription":"What does 2019 have in store for our favorite celebrities?\n","seoTitle":"Suggested New Year’s Resolutions for Ariana Grande, Prince George, and More","seoDescription":"What does 2019 have in store for our favorite celebrities?\n","channel":"Style","subChannel":"Celebrity","issueDate":"","ledeCaption":"","contentSource":"web","canonicalUrl":"","contentType":"","textMimeType":"","tags":[],"revisionAuthor":"Josh Duboff","meta":{"collectionName":"article