oth of whom have criticized Trump’s positions on immigration. An Obama spokesperson reportedly declined comment, though Obama himself has come out against the wall on numerous occasions. Carter, like Obama, has pushed for technological advancements to strengthen U.S. border security, according to <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2019/01/04/us/politics/trump-wall-shutdown.html\"><em>The New York Times</em></a>, but not the kind of wall that Trump is seeking $5 billion to build. A senior administration official reportedly suggested that Trump was “referring to public comments his predecessors have made about the need for border security, not necessarily for a wall specifically.”</p>","rubric":"Wall Tales","socialTitle":"Former Presidents Deny Supporting Border Wall, Despite Trump Claims","socialDescription":"Neither Bush nor Clinton ever shared Trump’s desire for a wall along the U.S.-Mexico border, spokespeople counter.","seoTitle":"Former Presidents Deny Supporting Border Wall, Despite Trump Claims","seoDescription":"Neither Bush nor Clinton ever shared Trump’s desire for a wall along the U.S.-Mexico border, spokespeople counter.","channel":"News","subChannel":"Politics","issueDate":"","ledeCaption":"","contentSource":"web","canonicalUrl":"","contentType":"","textMimeType":"","tags":["donald trump","border wall","bill clinton","barack obama","george w. bush"],"revisionAuthor":"Cynthia Orgel","meta":{"collectionName":"articles","modelName":"article","publishable":true,"identifiable":true,"image":false,"archived":false,"hallable":true,"hierarchical":false},"interactiveOverride":"","id":"5c30d260959bec2d411a495f","revision":14,"createdAt":"January 5, 2019 10:50 am","modifiedAt":"January 7, 2019 10:41 am","revisionCreatedAt":"January 7, 2019 10:41 am","_embedded":{"categories-channels":[{"fields":{"name":"News","slug":"news","revisionAuthor":"aviator-scripts-categories-migration","meta":{"collectionName":"categories","modelName":"category","publishable":false,"identifi