"id":"5c5ca4a93e8456443c337f33","revision":1,"createdAt":"February 7, 2019 4:35 pm","modifiedAt":"February 7, 2019 4:38 pm","revisionCreatedAt":"February 7, 2019 4:38 pm","altText":"INAUGURATION BALLS 11","description":"","caption":"Donald and Melania Trump take the​ir first dance, to &quot;My Way,&quot; a​t the Liberty Ball in Washingt​on D.C., January 20, 2017.","tags":[],"modelName":"photo","collection":"photos"}]},"pubDate":"February 7, 2019 4:47 pm","related":[],"template":"default","url":"/news/2019/02/behind-the-scenes-of-trumps-107-million-inauguration","videos":{}},{"hed":"Congresswoman Ilhan Omar Apologizes for Anti-Semitic Comments After Pelosi Brings Down the Hammer","promoHed":"A.O.C. Ally Apologizes After Being Accused of Anti-Semitism","dek":"The Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez ally was accused of using anti-Semitic tropes when criticizing AIPAC.","promoDek":"Congresswoman Ilhan Omar was forcefully criticized by Democratic leadership for her comments about Israel.","body":"<p>Freshman Congresswoman <strong>Ilhan Omar</strong> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/IlhanMN/status/1095046561254567937\">apologized</a> on Monday afternoon after she was forcefully criticized by <strong>Nancy Pelosi</strong> and House Democratic leadership for her use of what has been described as anti-Semitic language about AIPAC, the powerful pro-Israel lobbying group. “We have to always be willing to step back and think through criticism, just as I expect people to hear me when others attack me for my identity. That is why I unequivocally apologize,” she wrote, while maintaining that the role of lobbying groups in Washington is “problematic,” and “we must be willing to address it.”</p>\n<p>Omar drew fire from Democrats Monday for allegedly leaning into <a href=\"https://www.jweekly.com/2013/04/12/jews-and-money-the-stereotype-the-history-the-reality-jccsf-series-explores/\">harmful stereotypes</a> when she accused Rep. <strong>Kevin McCarthy</strong> of being under the influence of the American Israel Public Affairs Committee. (“It’s all about the Benjamins, baby,” she <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ilhanmn/status/1094747501578633216\">tweeted</a>, implying AIPAC had nudged McCarthy into censuring her for comments critical of Israel.) Jewish committee chairs <strong>Jerry Nadler, Eliot Engel,</strong> and <strong>Ted Deutch</strong> condemned her tweet, while two other Jewish representatives&#8212;<strong>Josh Gottheimer</strong> and <strong>Elaine Luria</strong>&#8212;circulated a letter expressing their alarm by “recent rhetoric from certain members.”</p>\n<p>Leadership, apparently, was listening. In a <a href=\"https://twitter.com/desiderioDC/status/1095025394011553798\">statement</a> released early Monday afternoon, the entirety of the Democratic leadership&#8212;House Speaker Pelosi and Majority Leader <strong>Steny Hoyer</strong> chief among them&#8212;unanimously called for Omar to “immediately apologize for these hurtful comments,” a remarkable rebuke. “Anti-Semitism must be called out, confronted, and condemned whenever it is encountered, without exception,” they wrote, affirming that they encouraged “legitimate criticism of Israel’s policies” on free-speech grounds. “But Congresswoman Omar’s use of anti-Semitic tropes and prejudicial accusations about Israel’s supporters is deeply offensive.”</p>\n<div class=\"embed block row social-twitter\"><blockquote class=\"embed twitter-embed-component twitter-tweet twitter-tweet\" lang=\"en\" data-type=\"twitter\" data-url=\"https://twitter.com/IlhanMN/status/1095046561254567937\"><p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/IlhanMN/status/1095046561254567937\">https://twitter.com/IlhanMN/status/1095046561254567937</a></p></blockquote></div><p>The wrist-slap might not have come at all, had this been Omar’s first offense. But the Minnesota representative has faced backlash before for remarks pertaining to Israel. In a 2012 tweet, she <a href=\"https://twitter.com/ilhanmn/status/269488770066313216\">wrote</a> that Israel has “hypnotized the world” and prayed that “Allah awaken the people and help them see the evil doings of Israel.” When the tweet <a href=\"https://www.jta.org/2018/07/09/politics/muslim-candidate-congress-calls-israel-apartheid-regime\">resurfaced in 2018</a>, Omar, a Somali refugee, defended her statement by arguing that the two were not equivalent: “Drawing attention to the apartheid Israeli regime is far from hating Jews.” After she assumed office and the scrutiny intensified, she claimed ignorance (“I don’t know how my comments would be offensive to Jewish Americans,” she <a href=\"https://freebeacon.com/issues/omar-defends-anti-israel-tweet-i-dont-know-how-my-comments-could-be-offensive-to-jewish-americans/\">told</a> CNN’s <strong>Poppy Harlow</strong> in January), and later said she was still learning. “I was like, ‘Do not call me that, that’s not what I was doing.’ And I was like, ‘Oh, I see what you’re saying now,’” she <a href=\"https://www.thedailybeast.com/ilhan-omar-addresses-anti-israel-comments-on-daily-show\">told</a> <em>The Daily Show</em>’s <strong>Trevor Noah</strong> earlier this month. “So I had to take a deep breath and understand where people were coming from and what point they were trying to make, which is what I expect people to do when I’m talking to them about things that impact me or offend me.”</p>\n<p>Omar’s most recent statement was interpreted more charitably by some left-leaning Jewish groups. The progressive organization J Street <a href=\"https://jstreet.org/press-releases/weaponization-and-oversimplification-of-israel-debate-must-end/#.XGHcQM9KhcC\">called</a> Monday’s controversy “overheated, ill-considered, and reductive,” arguing that the exchange “does nothing to advance the true interests and needs of Israelis or Palestinians, nor those of the American Jewish community. Lawmakers should be “extremely aware that tropes about Jewish money and political influence have been used for centuries to target and stigmatize” Jewish people, the group said in a statement, but they should “also refrain from labeling all criticism of Israeli actions or policies as ‘anti-Semitic,’ in a transparent effort to silence legitimate discussion and debate.” (Pelosi, for her part, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SpeakerPelosi/status/1095026564503343104\">said</a> she had met with Omar on Monday, and that both had come away “agree[ing] that we must use this moment to move forward as we reject anti-Semitism in all forms.”)</p>\n<p>But Omar’s slipups have given conservatives an opening to rip into the 37-year-old congresswoman, a staunch progressive ally of <strong>Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez.</strong> “Good that some Dems have condemned the disgraceful anti-Semitic remarks of Rep. Omar&#8212;but their words are empty unless Dem leaders remove her from the Foreign Affairs Committee,” <a href=\"https://twitter.com/SteveScalise/status/1095013990781079552\">wrote</a> Rep. <strong>Steve Scalise.</strong> “No one with her anti-Semitic views should be allowed to represent U.S. foreign policy.” In his initial threat to sanction Omar, McCarthy pointed to his own recent censure of Rep. <strong>Steve King</strong> after the Iowa congressman seemingly defended the terms “white nationalism [and] white supremacism.” “I think you’ve seen from my own actions that I take action about it,” McCarthy told reporters last Friday, despite being accused of <a href=\"https://www.cnn.com/2018/10/28/politics/tom-steyer-mccarthy-tweet/index.html\">trafficking in anti-Semitic tropes himself</a>. “I think when they stay silent, they are just as guilty.”</p>\n<h3>More Great Stories from <em>Vanity Fair</em></h3>\n<p>&#8212; The leaking, gossiping, and infighting that <a href=\"https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2019/01/trump-aide-recalls-conways-leaking-tactics-in-the-west-wing-vipers-nest?inline\">made Kellyanne Conway a formidable White House player</a></p>\n<p>&#8212; Why old news habits must die&#8212;so that <a href=\"https://www.vani