"><div class=\"wrapper\"><iframe height=\"360\" width=\"640\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UUrZ6WSlIqk\" allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\"> </iframe></div></div><p>Try not to jizz in your pants: the Lonely Island has announced its first multi-city tour, which will begin this summer.</p>\n<p>The comedy trio&#8212;__ Akiva Schaffer, Andy Samberg,__ and <strong>Jorma Taccone</strong>&#8212;first formed in 2001, and found mainstream success after being hired by <em>Saturday Night Live,</em> where they produced digital shorts including “Natalie’s Rap” and “Dick in a Box.” The group has released four studio albums in total, including the soundtrack to the 2016 film, <em>Popstar: Never Stop Never Stopping.</em> Until last year, however, they had never performed live together.</p>\n<p>Last summer, Samberg, Schaffer, and Taccone reunited for a live show at Comedy Central’s Clusterfest. The event was a comedic feat in itself: how do you satirize concerts while also putting on an entertaining concert? Successfully, it seems; Vulture’s <strong>Jesse David Fox</strong> noted in his <a href=\"https://www.vulture.com/2018/06/the-lonely-island-first-concert-ever-clusterfest-review.html\">review</a> that the group embraced its goofy qualities to put on, as Fox affectionately put it, “a big dumb show.”</p>\n<p>Now, one year later, the guys are going on tour for two weeks. Their multi-city adventure will kick off in June at Bonnaroo in Manchester, Tennessee, on June 15, with eight dates in cities including Washington, D.C., New York City, and Philadelphia. Tickets go on sale March 1, and fans can also register as “<a href=\"https://twitter.com/thelonelyisland/status/1098239537778634752\">Verified Fans</a>” to access pre-sale tickets. The complete list of tour dates is included below. <strong>Michael Bolton,</strong> if you’re reading this, a modest plea: please get in on this tour.</p>\n<p>June 15: Manchester, TN</p>\n<p>June 18: Washington, D.C.</p>\n<p>June 19: 